description:
drh added on 2014-09-24 11:57:08:
The following SQL code causes a segfault while running the INSERT statement:
CREATE TABLE t1(a text, b text DEFAULT(?1));
INSERT INTO t1(a) VALUES('hello');
SELECT * FROM t1;
This problem appears to have been introduced in SQLite version 3.6.14, over
five years ago.  The problem was reported on the sqlite-users mailing list
by Nathaniel Trellice.
